# Convert Student Concentration Detection to Web API + Adaptive Frontend

Convert the desktop OpenCV application into a **FastAPI WebSocket backend** + **adaptive HTML/CSS/JS frontend** that captures webcam frames in the browser, sends them for ML processing, and displays concentration data in a stunning real-time dashboard.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Browser Webcam] -->|Base64 frames via WebSocket| B[FastAPI Backend]
    B -->|MediaPipe + OpenCV processing| C[ML Engine]
    C -->|JSON concentration data| B
    B -->|WebSocket response| D[Frontend Dashboard]
```

**Key design decision**: The webcam capture happens **in the browser** using `getUserMedia`, frames are sent as base64-encoded images to the backend via WebSocket, and the backend returns JSON state data — no video streaming from the server. This keeps the backend stateless and deployable anywhere.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — FastAPI WebSocket API

#### [NEW] [app/\_\_init\_\_.py](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/app/__init__.py)
Empty init file for the `app` package.

#### [NEW] [app/ml_engine.py](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/app/ml_engine.py)
Extract all ML logic from [main.py](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/main.py) into a reusable class `ConcentrationDetector`:
- `__init__()` — initialize MediaPipe FaceMesh, state variables, session history
- `process_frame(frame: np.ndarray) -> dict` — accept a raw frame, run all detection (EAR, head pose, gaze, state classification, score), return JSON-serializable result
- `get_session_summary() -> dict` — return session analytics
- `reset_session()` — reset state for new session
- All helper functions from [main.py](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/main.py) become methods or stay as module-level utilities

#### [NEW] [app/api.py](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/app/api.py)
FastAPI application:
- `GET /` — serve the frontend `index.html`
- `GET /health` — health check endpoint
- `WebSocket /ws` — real-time frame processing:
  - Client sends: `{ "image": "<base64-encoded-jpeg>" }`
  - Server responds: `{ "state": "Focused", "concentration": 85, "ear": 0.28, "yaw": 5.2, "gaze_h": 0.48, "face_detected": true }`
- `GET /api/session` — get current session summary
- `POST /api/session/reset` — reset session data
- Static file mounting for frontend assets
- CORS middleware for cross-origin support

#### [MODIFY] [requirements.txt](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/requirements.txt)
Add: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `python-multipart`, `websockets`

---

### Frontend — Adaptive Web Dashboard

#### [NEW] [frontend/index.html](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/frontend/index.html)
Single-page app with:
- Webcam video preview with face detection overlay
- Real-time concentration state badge (color-coded)
- Concentration score gauge/arc
- Metrics panel (EAR, Yaw, Gaze values)
- Session timeline chart
- Responsive layout (mobile → desktop)
- SEO tags, proper heading hierarchy

#### [NEW] [frontend/style.css](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/frontend/style.css)
Modern, premium CSS design:
- Dark theme with glassmorphism panels
- CSS custom properties for theming
- Responsive breakpoints (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Smooth animations and transitions
- Concentration bar with gradient colors
- State badge animations (pulse effects)
- Google Font (Inter)

#### [NEW] [frontend/app.js](file:///e:/webd/Edu/ML-Backend/frontend/app.js)
JavaScript logic:
- WebSocket connection management (connect, reconnect, heartbeat)
- `getUserMedia` webcam capture
- Canvas-based frame capture and base64 encoding
- Real-time UI updates from WebSocket responses
- Concentration score history chart (canvas-based)
- Session timer and analytics
- Responsive menu/controls

